		<section>
			<section.front>
				<doc.title toc-guid="I86352a945ef311e0b1b20000837bc6dd">
					<head parent="doc.title">
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<label.name>§ </label.name>
						<label.designator>1:1.</label.designator>
						<headtext>In general</headtext>
						<eos/>
						<eop/>
					</head>
				</doc.title>
			</section.front>
			<section.body>
				<para>
					<bop/>
					<bos/>
					<paratext>While a pre-incorporation agreement is not legally required, it can be very useful in the process of forming a new corporation. <eos/>
						<bos/>There are few statutory provisions relating to contracts to create a corporation. <eos/>
						<bos/>As the courts have seldom passed on such contracts, there is little governing law on the subject other than the law relating to promoters.[<eos/>
						<bos/>
						<footnote.reference refid="Ib95f47f05e2d11eaa6968f05d1177892">1</footnote.reference>] Of course, the question as to whether it is desirable to create a corporation must receive careful consideration in the light of the particular situation. <eos/>
						<bos/>In making the choice of a business organization, tax considerations may be controlling, particularly in the case of a small closely-held corporation.[<eos/>
						<bos/>
						<footnote.reference refid="Ib95fbd215e2d11eaa6968f05d1177892">2</footnote.reference>] There are important factors to consider regarding the comparative tax advantage under state and federal laws of operating a business as a partnership, a corporation, or a limited liability company. <eos/>
						<bos/>Many factors must be considered, such as the following: the estimated net annual earnings of the business before taxes; the income of the business associates from outside sources; the amounts to be withdrawn from the business through salaries and by way of dividends. <eos/>
						<bos/>Moreover, the annual tax cost of conducting the business under the corporate and partnership form, generally at several projected levels of income, must be computed in the particular case by one well-versed in the current tax laws.<eos/>
					</paratext>
					<eop/>
				</para>
			</section.body>
		</section>
